---
// FAQ Section
---

<section class="py-24 lg:py-32 bg-background">
  <div class="container max-w-4xl">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-6xl font-display font-bold mb-6 leading-tight">
        FAQ
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-text-muted">
        Common questions answered
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Items -->
    <div class="space-y-0">
      <!-- Question 1 -->
      <details class="group border-b border-border py-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-xl lg:text-2xl font-bold hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity list-none flex justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <span>IS THIS TEMPLATE REALLY FREE?</span>
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="pt-4 text-lg text-text-muted">
          Yes! This template is completely free and open source under the MIT License. You can use it for personal projects, commercial work, or modify it as you see fit.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 2 -->
      <details class="group border-b border-border py-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-xl lg:text-2xl font-bold hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity list-none flex justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <span>DO I NEED TO KNOW ASTRO?</span>
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="pt-4 text-lg text-text-muted">
          Basic knowledge helps, but you can get started immediately by just editing the configuration file and writing blog posts in Markdown/MDX. The documentation guides you through everything.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 3 -->
      <details class="group border-b border-border py-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-xl lg:text-2xl font-bold hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity list-none flex justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <span>CAN I CUSTOMIZE THE DESIGN?</span>
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="pt-4 text-lg text-text-muted">
          Absolutely! The template uses Tailwind CSS, making it easy to customize colors, fonts, spacing, and layout. The code is clean and well-organized for easy modifications.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 4 -->
      <details class="group border-b border-border py-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-xl lg:text-2xl font-bold hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity list-none flex justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <span>WHERE CAN I DEPLOY THIS?</span>
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="pt-4 text-lg text-text-muted">
          Deploy anywhere that supports Node.js! Popular options include Vercel, Netlify, Railway, DigitalOcean, or any VPS. The template includes deployment examples in the documentation.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 5 -->
      <details class="group border-b border-border py-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-xl lg:text-2xl font-bold hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity list-none flex justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <span>MULTIPLE LANGUAGES?</span>
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="pt-4 text-lg text-text-muted">
          Yes! The template is internationalization (i18n) ready. You can easily add multiple language versions of your content and the interface automatically adapts.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 6 -->
      <details class="group border-b border-border py-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-xl lg:text-2xl font-bold hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity list-none flex justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <span>HOW DO I GET SUPPORT?</span>
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="pt-4 text-lg text-text-muted">
          Check the documentation on GitHub, open an issue if you find bugs, or start a discussion for questions. The community is here to help!
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
